					<Text><![CDATA[Product Delivery]]></Text>
					<Font>
						<Name>SansSerif</Name>
						<Size>26</Size>
						<Style>0</Style>
					</Font>
					<Alignment>LEFT</Alignment>
				</Text>
				<Rectangle>
					<Id>1413289423422</Id>
					<Name><![CDATA[rectangle]]></Name>
					<X>0</X><Y>50</Y>
					<Label><X>10</X><Y>10</Y></Label>
					<PublicFlag>true</PublicFlag>
					<PresentationFlag>true</PresentationFlag>
					<ShowLabel>false</ShowLabel>
					<Lock>true</Lock>
					<DrawMode>SHAPE_DRAW_2D3D</DrawMode>
					<EmbeddedIcon>false</EmbeddedIcon>
					<Z>0</Z>
					<ZHeight>10</ZHeight>
					<LineWidth>1</LineWidth>
					<LineColor/>
					<LineMaterial>null</LineMaterial>
					<LineStyle>SOLID</LineStyle>
					<Width>1000</Width>
					<Height>550</Height>
					<Rotation>0.0</Rotation>
					<FillColor>-939524097</FillColor>
					<FillMaterial>null</FillMaterial>
				</Rectangle>
				<Text>
					<Id>1413378661866</Id>
					<Name><![CDATA[text]]></Name>
					<X>30</X><Y>70</Y>
					<Label><X>0</X><Y>-10</Y></Label>
					<PublicFlag>true</PublicFlag>
					<PresentationFlag>true</PresentationFlag>
					<ShowLabel>false</ShowLabel>
					<DrawMode>SHAPE_DRAW_2D</DrawMode>
					<EmbeddedIcon>false</EmbeddedIcon>
					<Z>0</Z>
					<Rotation>0.0</Rotation>
					<Color>-16777216</Color>
					<Text><![CDATA[This model simulates the Coupang product delivery service in South Korea.
When initialized, the model creates multiple agents that are used to simulate the delivery process.
Such agents include the agents for the locations/centers in which the simulation is seen to accumulate
 and distribute products, agents that transport the products from one location to another, agents that
 represent the product, and agents that represent the orders issued by the consumers.
The agents that represent the major locations, regarded as centers in this simulation,
 consist of the following: fulfillment centers, logistics centers, and distribution centers.
The fulfillment centers are locations in which the products are initially stored.
They are located in areas where the population is comparatively sparse.
The logistics centers are the intermediary locations that the products pass through before being distributed to the consumers.
These centers are located closer to densely populated areas.
The distribution centers are the local points in which we assume that the consumers are located in.
Due to the limitations in the simulation power of our tools, we decided to use local points
 instead of individual households to represent the endpoints of our delivery service simulation.
The agents that are in charge of transporting the products consist of three subgroups.
These are vehicles, local vehicles, and forklifts.
The vehicles are responsible for transporting products from the fulfillment centers to the logistics centers.
These agents are governed by rules specified by state charts.
The local vehicles transport the products from the logistics centers to the distribution centers.
These agents are governed by state charts as well.
The forklifts are the transportation agents that are responsible for storing and retrieving products in the storage units within the fulfillment centers.
There is only one agent for simulating the products themselves.
These agents were named “Tokens.”
Finally, the agents responsible for representing the orders issued by the consumers consist of orders and customer orders.
For this simulation, customer orders are generated at the distribution centers and sent to the logistics centers.
These customer orders are accumulated in the logistics centers and the information is sent to the fulfillment centers as orders.

The simulated process can be summarized as of the following.
A continuous stream of tokens is injected into the storage units in the fulfillment centers.
Customer orders are generated in the distribution centers and sent to the logistics centers.
The logistics centers tally up the results and send the accumulated information to the fulfillment centers as orders.
The fulfillment centers, when they have enough products in their storage units, load the products onto the vehicles.
The vehicles transport the products to the corresponding logistics centers.
The products are loaded onto the local vehicles and transported to the distribution centers.

Note:
The storage units have been simulated to stop receiving products once a certain threshold has been reached.
]]></Text>
					<Font>
						<Name>SansSerif</Name>
						<Size>10</Size>
						<Style>0</Style>
					</Font>
					<Alignment>LEFT</Alignment>
				</Text>
				<Text>
					<Id>1559749119782</Id>
					<Name><![CDATA[text11]]></Name>
					<X>730</X><Y>10</Y>
					<Label><X>0</X><Y>-10</Y></Label>
